From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 3 Jun 2026 22:16:39 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/core: (fixup) handle sysfs test_ctx on
 damon_commit_target_fail()

sysfs test_ctx doesn't have ops, but stilll evaluated as
target_has_piid() since the ops_id is 0 (DAMON_OPS_VADDR).  Hence the
failure handling function always returns for the test ctx.  Fix it.

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/core.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mm/damon/core.c b/mm/damon/core.c
index b6e1ab1992030..41e4c73c443c5 100644
--- a/mm/damon/core.c
+++ b/mm/damon/core.c
@@ -1403,7 +1403,7 @@ static void damon_commit_target_fail(struct damon_ctx *dst,
 
 	if (!damon_target_has_pid(src))
 		return;
-	if (damon_target_has_pid(dst))
+	if (dst->ops.cleanup_target)
 		return;
 	damon_for_each_target(target, dst) {
 		if (target == failed)
-- 
2.47.3

